
[1]spick

   SPICK AND SPAN, bright; shining; as a garment spick and span new, or
   span-new. brightness; spiccare, to shine; spiccar le parole, to speak
   distinctly; spicciare, to rush out, the radical sense of which is to
   shoot or dart. Span is probably from the root of spangle, a mirror.
